content.description: Starts in chimney past 2 bolts then couple nice horizontal pieces. Physical climbing with interesting body positioning and exciting top-out.
content.protection: Two bolts, .75, #1, also there's a .3 placent just before finish on left of crack.
content.location: Wide, short crack on right side of detached tooth of rock separated from main wall.

climbs.name: Berry Queen
climbs.fa: Scott Duemler, Alexis Ely, Michael Genovese

content.description: Good rock with occasional sand dusting. Mixed route, 4 bolts and 3 or 4 cams. Steep Offwidth crack but climbs like a sport route with a lot of crimps and stemming outside of crack. Fun from beginning to end. Starts on right side chimney, a nice .4 or .5 protects up high, then a #3 or #4 to protect move onto sandy ledge. Continue past 4 bolts then one or two more cams to protect finishing moves, .3 to .5 depending on where you put it. Also you may opt to start the climb using the pumpkin patch variation, a lower angle but harder to protect start angling up from the left. The route name was inspired by climber Rachel Hall, because all her friends know she's the sweetest!
content.protection: 4 draws, cams sizes .3, .4, .5, & 4, season with alpine draws to taste ;)
content.location: On left side of the large tooth-like rock at Finders keepers area. The crack is easily seen from the creek below.

content.description: From sandy treadmill, head up sandy ramp to ledge. Sling the horn. Question its integrity. Traverse left into bomber jams. Gain a small ledge and fire into some ringlocks and fingers to finish.
content.protection: Doubles of. 3 - #2 and a single #3    Plus runners.
content.location: Up to the right of Toofer.

content.description: A tooth of rock with wide cracks on both sides and clean faces on either sides.
